1
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:11,867
<i> Who did this?</i>

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:14,933
<i>Grandmother, you're starting
to develop dementia.</i>

3
00:00:15,067 --> 00:00:19,433
<i>My plan was to rest first
so I could take care of you.</i>

4
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:21,900
<i> Don't do that.</i>

5
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:24,600
<i>I want the last image
I have of you</i>

6
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:27,700
<i>is seeing you wearing your
police uniform.</i>

7
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:29,033
<i> I wonder about that.</i>

8
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:30,100
<i> No regular job,</i>

9
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:33,467
<i>just participating in beauty
pageants,</i>

10
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,233
<i> but she's sophisticated.</i>

11
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:37,000
<i>I don't know how
she can afford that.</i>

12
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:38,567
<i>Maybe she's the Mayor's
mistress!</i>

13
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:42,100
<i> Okay, you're fooling them.</i>

14
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:44,500
<i> Oh my, don't believe him.</i>

15
00:00:44,633 --> 00:00:45,667
<i> He doesn't have a lover.</i>

16
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:49,567
<i>As for you, Selena,
your mouth is so tactless.</i>

17
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:52,667
<i>You don't need to lie just
to impress.</i>

18
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:54,567
<i>There are so many things
to like about you.</i>

19
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:57,000
<i>You know, Tonyo, we'll warn you.</i>

20
00:00:57,133 --> 00:01:00,800
<i>Bobby saw your selfie
with your girls</i>

21
00:01:00,933 --> 00:01:02,467
<i> who are allergic to clothes!</i>

22
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:04,633
<i>Oh my, that doesn't mean
anything!</i>

23
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:09,400
<i>But to an angry person,
everything has meaning.</i>

24
00:01:09,567 --> 00:01:12,600
<i>There are a lot of things
to like about me.</i>

25
00:01:12,733 --> 00:01:15,567
<i>Are you serious,
or are you just fooling me?</i>

26
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:18,200
<i>Of course!
Why would I lie?</i>

27
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:19,933
<i>Do you want me to bring you
home?</i>

28
00:01:20,067 --> 00:01:22,833
<i>It's late, it's dark,
it's dangerous.</i>

29
00:01:22,967 --> 00:01:23,833
<i> Okay!</i>

30
00:01:31,433 --> 00:01:34,100
Abdul, this is it.

31
00:01:34,233 --> 00:01:37,233
In fairness,
your friend is rich.

32
00:01:37,367 --> 00:01:38,267
She has no regular work,

33
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,133
and her only advantage
is her beauty.

34
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:42,133
And then she joins beauty
contests once a year.

35
00:01:42,267 --> 00:01:43,933
Mar, that's suspicious!

36
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:45,500
Hey, you're making such a noise!

37
00:01:45,633 --> 00:01:47,167
Maybe she's a contractor's
mistress!

38
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:48,300
Silly, she doesn't have
a boyfriend.

39
00:01:48,433 --> 00:01:49,767
Maybe she's the contractor
herself!

40
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:51,133
No way!

41
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:52,100
Let's go!

42
00:01:52,233 --> 00:01:53,667
She's really rich, isn't she?

43
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:54,200
Yes, she is.

44
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:55,300
Oh!

45
00:01:55,933 --> 00:01:57,000
The gate is open.

46
00:01:57,133 --> 00:01:58,467
Of course, they're expecting us.

47
00:01:58,600 --> 00:01:59,833
- Let's go!
- Right. Let's go!

48
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,533
- That's fine.
- Yes.

49
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:05,233
Donabel!

50
00:02:05,367 --> 00:02:07,633
- Let's party!
- Donabel!

51
00:02:40,867 --> 00:02:42,300
Donabel!

52
00:02:42,433 --> 00:02:43,733
Donabel!

53
00:02:45,133 --> 00:02:46,400
What did you do to her?

54
00:02:46,533 --> 00:02:47,333
Get away from her!

55
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,033
Apple, call the police, quick!

56
00:02:49,167 --> 00:02:49,900
Tell them...

57
00:02:50,033 --> 00:02:51,933
Tell me they killed
Miss Donabel!

58
00:02:52,067 --> 00:02:55,100
Hey, we didn't kill her!
We're not the killer!

59
00:03:05,533 --> 00:03:08,000
We're not killing anyone.

60
00:03:08,133 --> 00:03:10,267
Besides, I just told you

61
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:13,567
that we were just invited there
for some drinks.

62
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:15,500
Then that's what we found.

63
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,300
So you guys aren't close,

64
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:22,567
but you went there,
and it was late at night.

65
00:03:22,733 --> 00:03:23,867
Most likely.

66
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,233
We were supposed to drink.

67
00:03:26,367 --> 00:03:28,800
Of course, drinking starts late
at night, right?

68
00:03:28,933 --> 00:03:30,833
Oh my, Bobby is right.

69
00:03:30,967 --> 00:03:32,933
You're acting like a queen here
at Station 12.

70
00:03:33,067 --> 00:03:33,867
Yes.

71
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:37,533
Acting like a queen.

72
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:41,667
Well, sorry because I'm going
to handle this case.

73
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,233
Mar, Abdul!

74
00:03:43,367 --> 00:03:45,700
- Bobby! Help us.
- Bobby! Help us.

75
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:47,233
Don't bully them.

76
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:51,533
Please, Bobby.
I'm investigating.

77
00:03:51,667 --> 00:03:53,967
Don't favor them just because
they're your friends.

78
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:56,767
Hey, aren't their statements
enough?

79
00:03:56,933 --> 00:03:59,167
They weren't caught
in the act of a crime,

80
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:01,400
and they don't have criminal
records.

81
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:02,533
Yes, we don't have any.

82
00:04:02,667 --> 00:04:04,600
Yes, we do! We're good!

83
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:06,233
We don't have any cases
against us.

84
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:07,000
So?

85
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:10,367
They still need to go
through the process,

86
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,800
especially since there's
reasonable suspicion.

87
00:04:12,933 --> 00:04:15,400
They'll only be cleared
if it's proven

88
00:04:15,533 --> 00:04:17,367
that they weren't really
involved in the crime

89
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:18,033
that happened.

90
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:21,400
But for now,
they need to be detained.

91
00:04:21,533 --> 00:04:22,567
Detained?

92
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:25,233
No, that's not possible.
I can't.

93
00:04:25,367 --> 00:04:29,267
Abdul, I've been through a lot.
I can't add to this.

94
00:04:29,433 --> 00:04:30,200
Just a little more,

95
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:31,633
I'm about to shed tears
of blood.

96
00:04:31,767 --> 00:04:34,233
Bobby, help us.

97
00:04:34,367 --> 00:04:35,600
Have pity on us!

98
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:36,933
Bobby, no!

99
00:04:37,067 --> 00:04:39,733
- We're not doing anything!
- Okay, okay, don't worry.

100
00:04:39,867 --> 00:04:41,500
I'll help you.

101
00:04:41,633 --> 00:04:42,767
How?

102
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:45,000
When aren't you officially on
leave?

103
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:47,567
Then you'll resign.

104
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:49,167
How can you help?

105
00:04:57,433 --> 00:05:00,033
If you need anything,
just let me know.

106
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:01,100
Do you want to eat?

107
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:02,533
Water?

108
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:05,800
Hey, hey, hey.

109
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:08,700
What are you doing there?
Maybe you're nagging her.

110
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:11,967
- Go away.
- Sir is a nuisance.

111
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:13,067
You're still whispering.

112
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:14,933
How are you?

113
00:05:15,067 --> 00:05:15,767
Sir Eric.

114
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:17,033
Where's your companion?

115
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:19,900
She just went to comfort room.

116
00:05:20,033 --> 00:05:22,733
Her tummy always gets upset
whenever she's stressed.

117
00:05:22,867 --> 00:05:25,800
Sir Eric, did we do the right
thing?

118
00:05:25,933 --> 00:05:28,067
Maybe we just panicked.

119
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:30,867
If those two really
weren't guilty,

120
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,500
they'll be free too.

121
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,267
I'm still having goose bumps,

122
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:37,633
Sir, after seeing the look
on Miss Donabel's face.

123
00:05:37,767 --> 00:05:40,300
I can't get it out of my mind,
Sir Eric.

124
00:05:40,433 --> 00:05:41,167
Peach!

125
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,300
Sis!

126
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:43,633
Hey...

127
00:05:48,267 --> 00:05:49,367
What happened?

128
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,233
What are you doing there?

129
00:05:51,367 --> 00:05:54,200
We went to Miss Donabel's house.

130
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:57,767
I was just going to pay
the training fee for the pageant

131
00:05:57,900 --> 00:06:01,100
because we wanted
to join Miss Calabari.

132
00:06:01,233 --> 00:06:03,167
After that, we saw her.

133
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:06,233
But Mar and Abdul were there.

134
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:07,767
Mar and Abdul?

135
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:10,767
Does that mean they were
the killers?

136
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,467
I'm not sure.

137
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:21,167
Noble, go make Selena a cup
of coffee, the one from Arabia.

138
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:22,667
Okay, Sir.

139
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,600
Are you okay?

140
00:06:26,733 --> 00:06:28,767
Good Evening, Selena.

141
00:06:50,533 --> 00:06:51,300
Ouch!

142
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:16,133
Mar and Abdul.

143
00:07:16,267 --> 00:07:17,433
Have some coffee first.

144
00:07:17,567 --> 00:07:19,067
Sir!

145
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:22,333
Let us go! Have pity on us!

146
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:25,767
Sir, we don't want to be here
anymore! We can't sleep!

147
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:26,933
Just wait here.

148
00:07:27,067 --> 00:07:29,267
Sir, we need you right away.

149
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:31,200
Come on, please!

150
00:07:32,233 --> 00:07:33,700
- That's enough. Not like that.
- What?

151
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:34,633
Come on, have coffee.

152
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:36,667
- Don't leave us, Sir.
- Sir!

153
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:40,300
- We don't want to be here!
- That's enough. Come on.

154
00:07:40,433 --> 00:07:41,967
- Come on, Sir.
- That's enough.

155
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:44,433
- Come on. What's that?
- I'll go ahead.

156
00:07:44,567 --> 00:07:45,467
Sir, your...

157
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:51,500
- Sir, let us go.
- Yes.

158
00:07:54,733 --> 00:07:56,900
You are flirting with him.

159
00:07:57,033 --> 00:07:58,133
Can't you sleep too?

160
00:07:58,267 --> 00:08:00,500
Yes, it's hard.

161
00:08:00,633 --> 00:08:02,767
Why are we still here?

162
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:04,633
I'm not used to this.

163
00:08:08,367 --> 00:08:10,767
They're going to spend
the night at the precinct

164
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:13,033
until they're cleared.

165
00:08:13,167 --> 00:08:15,733
Grandmother,
those two are pitiful.

166
00:08:15,867 --> 00:08:16,967
Yes, that's right.

167
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:19,533
Maybe they're doing something
to Mar and Abdul.

168
00:08:19,667 --> 00:08:21,300
Maybe they're being punished.

169
00:08:21,467 --> 00:08:23,800
That's why you shouldn't resign.

170
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:37,467
Based on my analysis,

171
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:40,467
Donabel Custodio died
through strangulation.

172
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:44,767
Pressure was applied directly
to the neck by manual force.

173
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:48,467
I also found clear fingerprint
impressions on the skin.

174
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:52,367
Mar and Abdul's fingerprints
were negative.

175
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:55,600
So that means they have nothing
to do with this case.

176
00:08:55,767 --> 00:08:57,233
Let's check the CCTV.

177
00:08:59,367 --> 00:09:01,333
Forward here at 9:30 p.m.

178
00:09:02,633 --> 00:09:05,400
You'll see a man
wearing a cap enter.

179
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:08,000
Donabel opened the gate.

180
00:09:08,133 --> 00:09:10,000
There, they look like they know
each other.

181
00:09:12,033 --> 00:09:13,700
Forward to 10:15 p.m.

182
00:09:14,867 --> 00:09:19,267
That's when the man rushed out
of the house.

183
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,833
He was in such a hurry,
he didn't close the gate.

184
00:09:23,167 --> 00:09:25,467
This man's behavior
is suspicious.

185
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,033
Forward to 11 p.m.

186
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,467
That's when Mar and Abdul
arrived.

187
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,400
That's it. There.

188
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:39,967
My analysis estimated time of
death is at 10 p.m.

189
00:09:41,733 --> 00:09:44,033
Mar and Abdul arrived at 11 p.m.

190
00:09:45,133 --> 00:09:47,733
It looks like the unidentified
man on the CCTV

191
00:09:47,867 --> 00:09:49,233
is our primary suspect.

192
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:51,900
Look.

193
00:09:52,033 --> 00:09:55,367
Look at the back of his jacket,
the logo.

194
00:09:57,233 --> 00:09:59,033
That's the logo
of Binibining Calabari.

195
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:01,967
How did you know, Ma'am?

196
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:03,933
I watch that every year.

197
00:10:04,067 --> 00:10:06,433
That's why only the organizers
and staff have merch jackets

198
00:10:06,567 --> 00:10:08,133
because the pageant hasn't
started yet.

199
00:10:08,267 --> 00:10:13,400
That means our suspect is one of
the Binibining Calabari staff.

200
00:10:18,533 --> 00:10:21,200
Tonyo, it looks like we need
someone in the pageant.

201
00:10:21,333 --> 00:10:24,967
And the easiest way in
is to be a contestant.

202
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:27,800
Well, since I'm handling
this case,

203
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:29,633
I can volunteer to audition.

204
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,933
But what if you don't pass?

205
00:10:37,033 --> 00:10:38,833
Why? Am I not beautiful?

206
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:42,733
It's not like that,
Lieutenant Samson.

207
00:10:42,867 --> 00:10:45,600
Actually, Lieutenant Conde
is right.

208
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:47,267
We need another one to join.

209
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:50,700
Didn't they say, more entries,
more chances to win?

210
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:52,733
So who's the one auditioning,
Doc?

211
00:10:52,867 --> 00:10:54,233
It can't be you.

212
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:02,500
Me.

213
00:11:03,867 --> 00:11:06,867
I'm the other one auditioning
for Binibining Calabari.

214
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,233
It's Mar and Abdul,
do you believe that?

215
00:11:20,233 --> 00:11:21,233
I don't know.

216
00:11:21,367 --> 00:11:24,933
That's what Peach and Apple saw
at the crime scene.

217
00:11:25,067 --> 00:11:27,767
Don't those two seem kind?

218
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:32,700
Abdul, I don't think I can trust
him, but he's kind.

219
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:34,800
Besides, isn't he close
to Tonyo?

220
00:11:34,933 --> 00:11:36,033
Wait, wait a minute.

221
00:11:36,167 --> 00:11:37,633
How about Lieutenant Robles,

222
00:11:37,767 --> 00:11:40,433
isn't he a policeman
and handsome too?

223
00:11:40,567 --> 00:11:41,733
Look what happened.

224
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:45,067
Well, that's different.

225
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:47,433
There you go.

226
00:11:47,567 --> 00:11:50,800
It's always different when you
don't know how to answer.

227
00:11:50,933 --> 00:11:52,733
Go ahead and report to work.

228
00:11:52,867 --> 00:11:55,467
Just let me know
when you have news, okay?

229
00:11:57,100 --> 00:11:59,900
Okay, just be careful.

230
00:12:06,867 --> 00:12:08,400
Selena...

231
00:12:08,533 --> 00:12:10,433
Free...

232
00:12:10,567 --> 00:12:11,333
What?

233
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:15,600
- Can?
- What? Tell me!

234
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:16,933
I can leave now.

235
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:21,167
So shy.

236
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:23,433
Does this mean you're not going
to resign?

237
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:30,733
What's that, Bobby?

238
00:12:30,867 --> 00:12:32,067
Is it just your press release?

239
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:34,167
Just a way to get people
to talk about you?

240
00:12:36,067 --> 00:12:37,500
Lieutenant Samson,

241
00:12:37,633 --> 00:12:41,067
I have personal reasons
why I thought about resigning.

242
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,867
That's not a show-off.

243
00:12:44,467 --> 00:12:45,667
And if you think about it,

244
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,667
it seems like it's more
of an advantage for me

245
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:53,600
to join that pageant because
they thought I had resigned.

246
00:12:53,767 --> 00:12:54,967
How about you?

247
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:57,367
The killers are eyeing you

248
00:12:57,500 --> 00:13:00,833
because they know you're
an active-duty police officer.

249
00:13:00,967 --> 00:13:02,833
That's my problem.

250
00:13:02,967 --> 00:13:04,567
Can you do the other case?

251
00:13:06,667 --> 00:13:09,433
Well, our acting chief
put me here.

252
00:13:09,567 --> 00:13:11,733
He agreed to include me
in this case.

253
00:13:11,867 --> 00:13:14,167
There's nothing we can do,
Lieutenant Samson.

254
00:13:14,300 --> 00:13:15,833
Let's just work together.

255
00:13:15,967 --> 00:13:18,667
Don't worry,
Lieutenant Samson.

256
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:21,400
I'm not also happy to be
with you either.

257
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:24,000
I'm glad you're back,
Sergeant Enriquez.

258
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:28,667
Okay, let's plan this.

259
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:29,700
Dismissed.

260
00:13:32,867 --> 00:13:34,433
- Welcome back, Enriquez.
- Thank you.

261
00:13:35,567 --> 00:13:37,167
- Welcome back, Ma'am.
- Noble.

262
00:13:39,067 --> 00:13:40,700
Hi, Doc. Thank you, Doc.

263
00:13:44,467 --> 00:13:45,400
Bobby...

264
00:13:47,133 --> 00:13:51,300
I want you to know
that I'm glad you didn't resign.

265
00:13:52,067 --> 00:13:57,133
Don't think that I came back
here because of you.

266
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:01,700
I came back here for my dreams
and for my grandmother.

267
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:04,100
I know,

268
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,100
and I'm still happy.

269
00:14:31,933 --> 00:14:32,633
Mar...

270
00:14:33,933 --> 00:14:34,900
Mar, Abdul!

271
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,133
Abdul!

272
00:14:37,267 --> 00:14:38,300
Hey!

273
00:14:38,433 --> 00:14:39,533
Hey, wake up.

274
00:14:41,167 --> 00:14:42,200
Come on.

275
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:43,400
Boss Bobby!

276
00:14:43,533 --> 00:14:44,300
Bobby!

277
00:14:44,433 --> 00:14:46,133
- Are we free?
- What? Are we free?

278
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:48,767
Yes, you're free.

279
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:51,933
- Thank you!
- Thank you, Bobby!

280
00:14:52,067 --> 00:14:53,967
- I told you.
- Wait a minute.

281
00:14:54,933 --> 00:14:56,300
Why are you in uniform?

282
00:14:56,433 --> 00:14:57,000
Wait...

283
00:14:57,767 --> 00:15:01,300
Does this mean you're back
to work again?

284
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:03,533
Yes!

285
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:07,400
Perfect!

286
00:15:08,467 --> 00:15:12,367
And the first case I'll handle
is your ex's case.

287
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:15,367
We have a lead, but the suspect
doesn't have an ID yet.

288
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:19,800
But we have a hunch that he's
part of Binibining Calabari.

289
00:15:19,933 --> 00:15:21,800
Miss Calabari?

290
00:15:21,933 --> 00:15:23,567
What are you going to do, Bobby?

291
00:15:24,733 --> 00:15:29,100
Well, we need to enter
the Miss Calabari Foundation.

292
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:30,700
And for that to happen,

293
00:15:32,067 --> 00:15:34,367
maybe I need to join a pageant.

294
00:15:39,767 --> 00:15:40,933
Yes!

295
00:15:41,067 --> 00:15:42,233
You're something else, Bobby!

296
00:15:42,367 --> 00:15:43,633
You're a beauty pageant
contestant.

297
00:15:43,767 --> 00:15:45,367
Don't worry, Bobby.

298
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:48,267
Mar and I will take care of you,
right?

299
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:51,333
Really?

300
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:52,867
- Yes!
- Yes!

301
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:56,167
Madam, you have a gown fitting
scheduled today.

302
00:15:56,300 --> 00:15:57,700
Faye is also with us.

303
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:58,800
Okay.

304
00:15:58,933 --> 00:16:02,433
No, I don't need a new gown
for the event.

305
00:16:02,567 --> 00:16:05,533
Why are you sitting there?

306
00:16:05,667 --> 00:16:08,033
You've been in a bad mood
all day.

307
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,267
What's wrong?

308
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:12,633
Nothing, Mommy.

309
00:16:12,767 --> 00:16:14,233
Just don't mind me.

310
00:16:17,167 --> 00:16:19,733
Anyway, what's the gown for,
Auntie?

311
00:16:19,867 --> 00:16:23,367
Well, I was invited
to be one of the judges

312
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:25,900
in the upcoming Binibining
Calabari.

313
00:16:26,033 --> 00:16:28,167
It's one of Glen's highlight
projects.

314
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:31,067
Yes. It's the 20th
Binibining Calabari,

315
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,033
so the Municipal supports it.

316
00:16:33,167 --> 00:16:34,333
You know what?

317
00:16:34,467 --> 00:16:37,833
We have a murder case now
connected to that pageant.

318
00:16:37,967 --> 00:16:40,233
And the victim is a returning
candidate

319
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:41,867
of Binibining Calabari.

320
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:45,767
And we think that one of
the staff of the pageant

321
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:47,133
could be the killer.

322
00:16:47,267 --> 00:16:48,700
Who's the victim?

323
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:50,333
Donabel Custodio.

324
00:16:50,467 --> 00:16:54,067
But until now, we still don't
know what the motive was.

325
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:57,267
You know, I don't think it's
right to connect that case

326
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:59,800
to the people behind Binibining
Calabari.

327
00:16:59,933 --> 00:17:01,267
I think it's unfair.

328
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:05,000
But what about the victim?

329
00:17:05,133 --> 00:17:06,900
- What a pity.
- I understand.

330
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:08,633
The pageant is just starting,

331
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:11,733
and then the news of killings
is already tainted?

332
00:17:11,867 --> 00:17:14,167
It's not a good way
to start a pageant.

333
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:15,700
It's a milestone event.

334
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:19,833
What about the sponsors?
Maybe they'll back out.

335
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:23,133
And what about the charities
connected to the pageant?

336
00:17:23,267 --> 00:17:26,533
It's not like trying
to discredit the pageant, Glen.

337
00:17:26,667 --> 00:17:28,000
It's not like that.

338
00:17:28,133 --> 00:17:29,533
That's good, Cecilia.

339
00:17:29,667 --> 00:17:31,200
As the mayor of Calabari,

340
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:34,933
I'm looking out for the interest
and image of Calabari.

341
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:38,333
Do you understand?

342
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:42,833
Good.

343
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:50,933
Bobby won't resign.
That's good news.

344
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:52,367
Are you happy, Bok?

345
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:55,333
Bok, she's still angry with me.

346
00:17:55,467 --> 00:17:59,133
She said I wasn't the one
who advised her not to resign.

347
00:17:59,267 --> 00:18:03,967
But that's a good thing.
At least she won't resign.

348
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:09,233
How can Bobby not be mad at you?
You doubted her brother.

349
00:18:10,233 --> 00:18:13,800
Bobby wouldn't know that
if it weren't for you.

350
00:18:13,933 --> 00:18:15,367
You're so talkative.

351
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:18,467
Well, sorry.

352
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:22,867
I just forgot that Bobby
and the Mayor are siblings.

353
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,700
Bok, how are you?

354
00:18:26,833 --> 00:18:28,700
Are you still doubting him?

355
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:30,500
Yes, Bok.

356
00:18:30,633 --> 00:18:32,900
Garcia, do you remember
when we caught Robles?

357
00:18:33,033 --> 00:18:33,767
Yes.

358
00:18:33,900 --> 00:18:36,867
Robles called the Mayor "Boss."

359
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,567
Then the Mayor looked stunned.

360
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,233
<i> Boss...</i>

361
00:18:41,367 --> 00:18:42,200
<i> Mayor.</i>

362
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:45,667
Yes, that's right.

363
00:18:49,533 --> 00:18:50,867
No, no, no.

364
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:54,400
He said, "Boss Mayor".

365
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:57,633
That's what he's really called.
Of course, he's the Mayor.

366
00:18:57,800 --> 00:19:00,800
And that's what his people
always say to him.

367
00:19:00,933 --> 00:19:02,567
Yes, Bok.

368
00:19:02,700 --> 00:19:05,267
All the people in the
municipality call him

369
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:08,100
"Boss Mayor",
especially the sycophants.

370
00:19:09,067 --> 00:19:10,033
No, Bok.

371
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:13,067
My hunch about the Mayor
is really different.

372
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:15,533
I find his behavior fake.

373
00:19:15,667 --> 00:19:18,500
Bok, you don't have
any evidence.

374
00:19:18,633 --> 00:19:22,333
Besides, the Mayor has a lot of
support in Station 12.

375
00:19:22,467 --> 00:19:25,633
So Chief won't pay attention
to your hunches.

376
00:19:27,267 --> 00:19:28,933
And above all,

377
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:33,400
stop those bad thoughts you have
about the Mayor

378
00:19:33,533 --> 00:19:35,667
because it will only make Bobby
angrier with you.

379
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:37,900
She won't pay attention to you.

380
00:19:38,033 --> 00:19:39,100
So if I were you,

381
00:19:39,233 --> 00:19:43,033
stop those hunches so Bobby
won't get angry anymore.

382
00:19:47,133 --> 00:19:50,667
Speaking of love life,
I'll tell you something,

383
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,633
but don't be jealous, okay?

384
00:19:52,767 --> 00:19:53,967
Wait a minute, Bok.

385
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:55,467
It's a bit late.

386
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:57,900
Besides, I'm sleepy too.
I need to go home.

387
00:19:58,033 --> 00:19:59,233
Me too.

388
00:19:59,367 --> 00:20:02,233
Besides, I heard there's
a typhoon coming.

389
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:04,733
I can already feel the wind.
It seems...

390
00:20:04,867 --> 00:20:05,633
Let's go, let's go.

391
00:20:05,767 --> 00:20:07,400
We might get caught
in a typhoon.

392
00:20:07,533 --> 00:20:10,133
Is there a typhoon?
I'll check the news.

393
00:20:11,067 --> 00:20:11,933
Weather...

394
00:20:14,133 --> 00:20:15,400
There's nothing!

395
00:20:15,533 --> 00:20:16,500
Bok!

396
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:21,900
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

397
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,200
Good morning, Ma'am.

398
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:26,833
Peach.

399
00:20:26,967 --> 00:20:28,500
Dressing room B, Ma'am.

400
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:30,267
Me, Apple.

401
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:31,667
Dressing room A.

402
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:32,800
- There too?
- Yes.

403
00:20:32,933 --> 00:20:34,333
- Thank you!
- Thanks.

404
00:20:35,433 --> 00:20:36,633
Dressing room B.

405
00:20:50,967 --> 00:20:53,100
- Dressing room B.
- Dressing room.

406
00:20:53,233 --> 00:20:54,100
Good morning, Ma'am.

407
00:20:55,433 --> 00:20:56,600
Dressing room B.

408
00:21:01,733 --> 00:21:02,733
Charlie Samson.

409
00:21:02,867 --> 00:21:03,667
Charlie Samson...

410
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,233
Ma'am,
you're in dressing room B.

411
00:21:06,767 --> 00:21:09,233
Bobby Enriquez,
where's her dressing room?

412
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,900
Bobby Enriquez...

413
00:21:11,033 --> 00:21:12,700
She's in dressing room A.

414
00:21:12,833 --> 00:21:14,367
Can I just go there too?

415
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,400
You're in dressing room B,
Ma'am.

416
00:21:16,533 --> 00:21:18,067
I'm sorry, Ma'am. Thank you.

417
00:21:27,167 --> 00:21:28,433
Under maintenance.

418
00:21:28,567 --> 00:21:30,300
Why now, when I really need
to pee?

419
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:37,567
Anybody here?

420
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:39,233
Anybody here?

421
00:21:39,367 --> 00:21:41,433
I'm just going to use the CR.

422
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,233
The women's section is closed.

423
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:12,633
Hey! What are you doing here?

424
00:22:12,767 --> 00:22:13,967
You're a peeping tom,
aren't you?

425
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:14,833
Miss, I'm not...

426
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:15,700
I'm not...

427
00:22:17,033 --> 00:22:17,700
Ouch.

428
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:39,733
If you could only eat one dish
for the rest of your life,

429
00:22:39,867 --> 00:22:40,433
what's that?

430
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:41,467
<i> Sinigang.</i>

431
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:42,767
Why?

432
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:47,333
Because like a sunflower that
turns its face into the sun,

433
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:51,900
I wish to turn my heart towards
those in need.

434
00:22:52,067 --> 00:22:53,500
This is your first time
in a pageant, right?

435
00:22:53,633 --> 00:22:54,300
Yes.

436
00:22:54,433 --> 00:22:55,033
Obvious?

437
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:56,233
Teresa, by the way.

438
00:22:56,367 --> 00:22:57,500
Bobby.

439
00:22:57,633 --> 00:22:59,700
What, Bobby? How are you?
Are you in?

440
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:02,700
Take a look at the two at the
end, especially the last one.

441
00:23:02,833 --> 00:23:04,033
You know her very well.

442
00:23:04,167 --> 00:23:06,967
Why would two police officers
want to join a beauty pageant?

443
00:23:07,100 --> 00:23:08,600
They have other agendas.
